title: [Whistler's Pass]
description: Vein-like cracks scar the surfaces of the otherwise smooth walls of the pass, evidence of  the tremendous toll placed upon them by the harsh elements of the region.  Although travelers are partially sheltered from frequent gusts of icy wind, the silent stone walls seem to emit a bone-numbing chill of their own.
